metadata.name: Pearls #36
metadata.description:
Pearls is a generative minimal artwork made with 100% code in p5js.

This algorithm places perfectly round pearls into multiple stacked grids and connects them in a pleasing way. The small grids lead to interesting emerging patterns. Some see faces and fish, others see ancient hardware and elephants, and some just enjoy the minimal simplicity.

-- controls (in live view)
s: to save the current image
a: to play a small animation

-- some attributes
layout: 2x2 to 34x34
palette: genuary, monochrome red & purple, night
mode: ink, walk
bias: central, north, east, south, west
density: sparse, middle, dense
symmetry: none, vertical, horizontal, point
layer: 2 to 6

metadata.name: Anarchy #122
metadata.description:
"Anarchy" aims to pay tribute to the Impressionist masters and explore the interplay between randomness and control. My goal was to capture the bold use of color and the fleeting nature of light and movement that is so characteristic of the Abstract Impressionist style. 

This piece uses a total of 12 color palettes, each one inspired by a different Impressionist painter. Some artists have two palette variations, while others only have one.

I wanted to create something that was unique and that would reflect my own visual emotions while also paying homage to the artists that inspire me. "Anarchy" is part of my exploration of the relationship between randomness and intention, and a celebration of the enduring legacy of the Impressionist masters.

Made by wandurz using p5.js 
January 2023

metadata.name: Ray Drops #306
metadata.description:
Ray Drops plays with the idea of rays that are projected out from a random center point which oscillate at variable frequencies. At each inflection point it has a chance of being intersected by a ring. The inflection points vary in how closely they are spaced and can cluster around the center point or fan all the way out to the edges. 

When run this generative creates a 12 layer SVG vector that is designed to be run on a laser cutter in order to build an in real life woodcut. Each layer is a single contiguous piece with no floating elements so when cut out of wood you end up with 12 layers that can be secured with 10 Chicago screws.  

Learn more and get physical editions: https://alleditions.art/p/ray-drops

Shift P - exports a PNG
Shift S - exports SVG
Shift E - explodes the layers

The 5 rarest mints (once the series is minted out) will receive a free signed physical which can be claimed by an owner of the NFT at anytime. It can be left attached and claimed by any future owner. 

I will also be giving away 5 free signed physicals randomly to people who tweet a picture of their edition and tag @shawnkemp

metadata.name: Shattered Reality  #31
metadata.description:
Black holes, collapsing stars.
What happens as you approach a celestial event, where space is folding on itself?

This work is a graphic representation of that phenomenon.
With a nod to the '80s, cosmos, black holes and the space shuttle age.
Optimism and Reality.


Made with p5js - Jan 2023

S to save 1000x1000
H to save 2000x2000 - takes a little time
U to save 4000x4000 - takes until the end of the universe, or longer.
A to animate in again.

metadata.name: Lux Lucet #4
metadata.description:
"Lux in tenebris lucet et tenebrae eam non comprehenderunt" - Latin for "The Light shines in the darkness, and the darkness did not comprehend it"

Crafted with code in p5js on random Cellular Automata structures, a tribute to Leonardo da Vinci and Fibonacci, these implied landscapes revolve around the magic of PI. All iterations are unique, 90% of them are monochromatic and there is 10% chance of a red interference.

"The breadth and length of shadow and of light, although through foreshortening it may appear less in quantity, will not therefore appear diminished as to quality either in respect of brightness or darkness." Leonardo Da Vinci

Press "s" to save a larger PNG file for print (5x current viewport size)

metadata.name: Arcane #5
metadata.description:
Our lives are dreamed by incredible machines, our decisions can be predicted long before we think we made them. We are leaves floating in a pulsating energy ocean. Love and anger are pointless drops of color in it. But we believe in reason. It's laughable.

---------------

This is an endless animation that while it never repeats itself maintain a distinct character driven by the seeded hash.

The work is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- space bar : pause/resume animation
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution

Don't forget, if you want to capture a certain image, use the spacebar to pause and resume the animation.
